# Keep the build context to what the image actually needs: the Go sources for
# the CLI, and tests/hwsim's scripts.
#
# Excluding .git matters most. A fresh `git clone` produces a different .git
# every time (new pack files, new refs), so with it in the context `COPY . .`
# misses the layer cache on every CI run - rebuilding the toolchain stage and
# leaving a fresh set of dangling images behind each time.
.git
.github
docs
dev
examples
*.md
